headline: Alaska Air Stock Flies High on Strong Guidance and $1 Billion Share Buyback Program
summary: Alaska Air Group  stock soared Tuesday after the company offered strong earnings guidance for 2025 and approved a $1 billion share repurchase program.  Shares of the airline holding company gained 13% to $61.05, on pace for their highest close since Oct. 6, 2021, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  The rally came after  Alaska Air  issued an optimistic financial outlook in its first presentation for investors since it completed its acquisition of Hawaiian Holdings in September.
